1. Monitoring Server Performance with Task Manager


Task Manager gives you a real-time view of your systemâ€™s performance, including CPU, memory, disk, and network usage.

Opening Task Manager:
Press Ctrl + Shift + Esc to open Task Manager.
Alternatively, Ctrl + Alt + Del and then select Task Manager.
You can also right-click the taskbar and choose Task Manager from the menu.

